             2. Remote(github) repo
How do I create a git repo?

    git init --> create an empity git repo
how to save your codes/files on git repo?
   1. Create a class / change a class
   2. add the file/class to staging area
       git add . --> "." everything

   3. Commiting / take snapshot + put them in git repo
           git commit -m "message"
           if you created a class:
            "add Login.java, upaate pom.xml"

           if you made changes :
           "update Login.java"
           "delete Logout.java"
           "config.properties "
           "a.json"
open a class -> add --> commit
---------------
I do not know where to start to save my code to git repo? do not know write which command?
        git status
how do I know how many commit I had?
       git log
-------------------
Task1 :
1. create a class : Spring
2. Add all modified classes/files into staging area
        git add .

3. Commit the changes
       git commit -m "add Spring.java"
4. see how many commits you have
      git log
--------------
Mac : clear
Windows : cls = clear screen
or
ctrl + l
git commit -a = git add + git commit -m
git commit -a ""
====================
1. we need 2 repo for 1 project :
  1. git(local) repo
             git init
  2. github(remote) repo
       go to github , clicl "+"
---------------------
fatal: remote origin already exists.
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/Asiya59/gitLearning.git
git push -u origin master
---------------------
Task 2: push a class to github
1. Create a class -> Winter
2. add it to staging area
       git add .
3. commit it
       git commit -m "add Winter.java"
4. push it to github
       git push
---------------------------
Summary:
1. Create a project
2. we need a local repo (git)
      terminal: git init
3. we need a remote repo (github)
      github: click + , new repo + repo name , it same as project name
4. create a class/file

5. add them in staging area
      git add .
6. commit the changes
      git commit -m "leave message"
7. push it to github
      git push
--------
